  "prompt": "What does it happen when an illegal immigrant in US goes to the airport to take a plane and come back in his country?",
  "response": "When an undocumented immigrant attempts to go through airport security and travel internationally, several potential scenarios could occur:\n\n1. If they have a valid passport from their home country:\n- They may be allowed to leave the US\n- However, re-entry will be extremely difficult or impossible\n\n2. If they lack proper documentation:\n- They might be detained by TSA or airport security\n- Customs and Border Protection (CBP) could be contacted\n- They may face potential legal consequences\n- They could be prevented from boarding the flight\n\n3. Potential consequences:\n- Possible arrest and deportation proceedings\n- Being placed on a watchlist\n- Future travel restrictions\n- Potential bars from re-entering the US for several years\n\n4. Safest approach:\n- Consulting an immigration lawyer\n- Exploring legal pathways for documentation\n- Understanding potential risks before attempting international travel\n\nThe specific outcome depends on individual circumstances, current immigration policies, and individual case details. Each situation can be complex and unique.\n\nIt's always recommended to seek professional legal advice for personalized guidance regarding immigration matters.",
